content: Loved the game back in '14 and I am really happy to see it on Android. content: I love the art style of the game, it looks and feels very fun. The gameplay is also very good, the carnage is wonderful. One of the best looking TD games I've played on mobile so far.     BUT, the fact that I paid full price for the game should not mean I have to pay extra for in game items. Either put your game on the market for a fixed price OR make it free with ads or micro-transactions. Personally I prefer the first one.  I understand the need for funding, but this is ridiculous. I've paid full price for the game. I should not be expected to pay anything else to experience the game in full. Things that can be unlocked now with 'gems' or whatever they are should be unlocked naturally as you progress through the game.  I see on your website that you are "indie game developers" so I expect better from you.   This game deserves a better rating, but only if it drops the "in-game purchases" bullsh*t.  Later edit: you also replied to another 2 star review asking why there are IAPs that it's just a way for the impatient players to beat the game faster. But you could do this with a cheat code system or something... not expecting the player to pay real money for that.
replyContent:
hey Stefan
we dont want players to get everything right away as there's less incentive to keep playing. We're planning on adding another 10+ levels to take it to 35+ & endless modes so the weapons and items have been priced for that length. If you have access to everything it makes the them less special. We want the choices you make to matter

content: When I try a new TD game, there are two things most important- it being extremely satisfying to watch your turret battery now down enemies, and bulk of content to keep the game interesting for long periods of time. Too often, I'll try some new iteration of tower defense only to find there are 4 tower types with 1 upgrade each, and they all unsatisfyingly pew-pew-pew away at your enemies. Not so with OTTTD. This is certainly one of the best offerings I've seen of the genre, and I'm only halfway through!
replyContent: Thanks Adam. You are the TD fan we made this for. Someone who wanted something new and glad to hear you enjoyed it. Look out for more updates soon!

content: Great play. Needs some stability issues fixed but fun to play. A few minor improvements will make it a five star easily.
replyContent: Thanks Joel. We're on those updates. We will earn that 5th star!

content: very nice games and design but laggy on galaxy s4 and also veru hard to find my soldier when the enemy dead because the floor so many dead enemy.please fix thelaggy
replyContent: We're on it Han, a gib reduction option coming. Thanks for the review.

content: Only on third level but I like seeing the bones and blood stack up

If you like em like I do, this TD is one of the best. Awesome graphics and smooth gameplay. People have complained about lack of alerts, but this game makes you multitask like a mother since there aren't any. Fine by me, just makes it harder.
replyContent: haha you have to pay attention that's for sure! thanks for the review. What can we do to get that 5th star? We want it :)

content: A decent classic tower defense game with heroes and lots of upgrades. Great art, animation and pacing.
great game. love the rpg aspects
I cant put it down its so fun

Hi, I have purchased the game 2 days ago and it's been ok so far, sort of. It has a few glithces. I am playing it on a Galaxy Tab 3 (10.1) and when I want to pause the game and press the power buton and then turn it back on, I get unlimited Ultra Tower power ups and Rockets the other hero abilities as well as 9.999.999 gold and 9.999 gems (or whatever they are). I am not upset about that, but as I finish the level and kill all the enemies, it does nothing. I can select the heroes, they talk, but they don't move. Tried pressing pause but it's not working either. The only good thing about it is I've managed to buy the expensive weapons :) I know this is not something you desire to "fix" in the user's favour, as the in app purchases would be useless, but it's information that hopefully will help you to improve the game. Rated 4 stars as there is no option yet to change graphic options. My tablet is getting a bit laggy when there are too many monsters and rockets on the screen. Otherwise, great gameplay. The dialogues could be a bit more diversified and would like to hear the heroes say more things.
Decent TD game with comical elements, glad to see Dev responses that they're  reducing the need for IAP. Interested to see where this game will be in 6 months, hoping to be impressed.
Great so far. Just as the name states. Looking forward to new levels and enhancements!
On nexus 7 it has serious performance issues which makes it nearly impossible to play when there are a lot of mobs on the map.

Very cool and neat game. I like it better than other TD games however I find it difficult to find my soldiers in all the mess or know when a tower is down. Picking my soldiers picture icon should select them. Lacks "identifiers" for when things happen. Other than that very cool and great game.

Great idea, gameplay is fun, needs to allow landscape rotation in either direction, graphics are great, but can get a little stuttery on my 2nd gen Nexus 7. With a bit more polish this could be my new favorite game.
Addicting and fast paced.  Wish matches were longer and more towers would be nice too
So cewl gam3 much wurf

Must say, took a shot on this game, very impressed. Reminds me of Kingdom Rush in a way, but with its own unique twist. Already beat a few levels and already love the game. Haven't had to use any IAP at all (not a fan of in general). Highly recommended, give it a try if you love tower defense games.

The game is OK, but there are a few problems. The biggest is about the corpses. After a few minutes of playing the map is basically filled with corpses and blood, which makes it very hard to see the enemies and heroes, and also makes the game very slow. Is there an option to disable it? Also, I don't see any RTS element here, it's basically a cheap copy of Kingdom Rush with a futuristic theme.
replyContent:
Hi Ricardo, we're adding an option to reduce the gibs if needed for slower devices. We're also optimising the code too in the next update.

As for RTS we have 3 heroes to control not one and each has a lot more optional than KR to both customize and to use as a weapon. We feel this is much closer to RTS than just moving one unkillable hero around.

content: A slightly new take on the genre. Easy to pick up with a great sense of humour.
Really good game, gameplay is excellent, reminds me of td sentinel. A lot of good humor :) P.s. I would like fast speed button though...

Feels like TD games have been around for as long as Bruce Forsythe. Once in a while you need something different to keep the idea fresh (unlike Bruce Forsythe). This game is a unique twist on the genre and is really bloomin fun. 10 Bruce's out of 10!
Stands in one line with a monster like Kingdom Rush. Great game, great graphics and dynamics. Love the idea of characters and love the towers. Good job. Just please add Play Games to it.

Very polished, very fun. The heroes act as mobile towers with special powers, supplementing the other towers you build. Hilarious writing and weirdly fun character design round it out.   I've seen a lot of people mentioning the in-app purchases, but I have played for 10 levels and have yet to feel the need for IAP, or even any in-game nudges towards it. There's definitely $3 worth of game here.  Seriously, there's a flying jet shark. What more do you want?
Really enjoy this game. my only problem is with te "gore". I like it, but puts strain on my hardware (Nexus 7 2013).
replyContent: We're adding a feature to have the gore be able to turned off for those that are squeamish and those that was the maximise the performance. Thanks for the review

content: The fact that you can't exit out of the app mid game, then go back into it is the main reason this got 4 stars instead of 5. It should also be a lot clearer that a tower has been completely destroyed because sometimes I go 2 minutes without even realising it, it'd be good if a little box came up saying its been damaged then has the option to repair it. Last thing is that it should have a graphics menu as there are a lot of particles and generally a good looking game. Good game though, like the gameplay.
replyContent: Thanks Jamie, we're working on updates now that include minor tweaks such as you described. Thanks for the review

content: Sure 2 become an instant cult classic in this genre. The comic blood & guts effects will blow u away! Easy 2 c this was a true labor of love & not just about the money. If u love T.D. u will love this, it's that simple. FUNTASTIC! 10/10
Like Russian Tank!
One of the best tower defence games ive ever played.

love the design, it looks really great on a tablet !  Can we get some Play Games achievements ? i would also like a G+ sign-in, for progress follow-up on different devices, like from my phone to my tablet...
replyContent: We're having trouble with plugins for G+ signin and other services so stick with us as we work to resolve them

content: This is the best TD style game i've ever played with great graphics! Only gripe is the gibs - if they can either be reduced or configured, that would be excellent!
replyContent: Update coming with optional gib reduction :)
